Here is a simple Julia function which implements this functionality. This function uses the `filter` function to filter out those words which satisfy the condition of starting with an upper case character. The `isuppercasefirst` function checks if the first character in the string is an upper case letter.

```julia
function keep_only_names(words::Vector{String})
    return filter(word -> isuppercasefirst(word), words)
end

function isuppercasefirst(s::AbstractString)
    if isempty(s)
        return false
    end
    first_char = s[1]
    return (first_char >= 'A' && first_char <= 'Z')
end
```
In the above function, `keep_only_names` takes a vector of strings as an input and returns another vector of string where only those words start with an upper case letter. The `isuppercasefirst` function checks if the first character in the provided string is an upper case letter or not. If it is then it returns true otherwise false.
